cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image representation learning using a novel architecture that integrates Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Dictionary Learning (DL) into a unified framework. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of multi-layer perception and stochastic gradient descent, which are common techniques in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to image representation learning, which could be of interest to researchers in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses simulations on real databases, which could also place it in the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM).
